icqsol
======

icqsol is a collection of tools for constructing and solving partial 
differential equations on the web.

How to build icqsol 
-------------------

Prerequisites
.............

* python. Version 2.7 will work
* numpy. Version 1.9.2 will work
* VTK with python wrapping enabled. Version 6.1.0 will work
* Pytriangle. Version 1.0 will work
* CMake

Installing ICQSol
.................

a) Let python choose the installation directory, typically 
   under /usr/lib/python<version>/site-packages. May require
   sudo privilege

$ cmake .

b) Install under ~/.local/lib/python<version>/site-packages/

$ cmake -DINSTALL_USER=ON .

c) Install in a user specified directory. Will require the user
to set PYTHONPATH

$ cmake -DINSTALL_PREFIX=ON -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=<myDirectory> .

How to test icqsol
------------------

You should be able to import icqsol in the python interpreter

$ python
Python 2.7.5 (default, Feb 11 2014, 07:46:25) 
[GCC 4.8.2 20140120 (Red Hat 4.8.2-13)] on linux2
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import icqsol
>>> 

More extensive tests can be run by typing

$ ctest


